  "prompt": "What is the legal status of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious federal crime in the United States, as well as in many other countries around the world. It's illegal under both federal and state laws, though the specific laws and penalties can vary.\n\n**Federal Law (United States):**\n\n*   **Title 18, U.S. Code, Section 1956 (Laundering of Monetary Instruments):** This is the primary federal statute addressing money laundering. It prohibits a wide range of activities involving the proceeds of unlawful activity, including:\n    *   Conducting financial transactions with the intent to promote criminal activity.\n    *   Conducting financial transactions knowing that the property involved represents the proceeds of some form of unlawful activity and with the intent to conceal or disguise the nature, location, source, ownership, or control of the proceeds.\n    *   Transporting monetary instruments or funds into or out of the United States with the intent to promote unlawful activity or knowing that the funds represent the proceeds of unlawful activity and",
